overview: A rare condition — face blindness — gives an eccentric yet incredibly gifted neurologist a unique perspective on care, fueling his mission to change the way people see his patients. Alongside a team of brilliant young interns, he solves some of the world's most puzzling psychological cases while navigating the complicated relationships that come with the job.

episodes.name: Pilot
episodes.overview: Dr. Oliver Wolf reluctantly accepts a job at Bronx General Hospital where he's forced to work with a team of interns as they treat a mother who can no longer recognize her children.

episodes.name: The Disembodied Woman
episodes.overview: When a high school girls' basketball coach faces a debilitating illness, Dr. Wolf must help her reconnect with her body before it's too late. Ericka and Dana treat a frat boy who sees dragons.

episodes.name: The Lost Biker
episodes.overview: A member of a biker gang seeks out Dr. Wolf's help as he grapples with life-threatening memory loss. The interns are tasked to help a young girl struggling with mysterious seizures.

episodes.name: The Blackout Bride
episodes.overview: When a bloody bride stumbles into Bronx General, Wolf races against the clock to save her and her missing husband. Ericka and Jacob fight to keep a John Doe patient in their care.

episodes.name: The Haunted Marine
episodes.overview: Wolf must help a Marine grapple with mysterious symptoms before the birth of his child.

episodes.name: The Girl Who Cried Pregnant
episodes.overview: Dr. Wolf and the interns go back to high school to treat a group of pregnant teenagers.

episodes.name: The Man From Grozny
episodes.overview: Dr. Wolf and the team perform their most experimental treatment yet: a brain-computer interface implantation in their John Doe patient's brain.

episodes.name: The Lovesick Widow
episodes.overview: When an elderly woman is brought in with signs of dementia, Dr. Wolf investigates whether she's suffering from a neurological disorder or having a late-in-life awakening; Dr. Pierce grapples with a chilling discovery about one of her patients.
